# Enrollify admin conventions

## Stack

- **Canonical admin UI:** Vite SPA at `/enrollify-manage` (`src/pages/admin/`, `src/lib/admin/`)
- **Legacy:** `apps/admin/` Next.js app is deprecated — do not extend
- **Hybrid data access:**
  - **Supabase (SPA):** auth session, own `staff_profiles` read/update/insert, email change via `updateUser`
  - **Express API (`/api/admin/*`):** leads, notes, analytics, AI providers, exports — via `src/lib/admin/api.ts`

## Auth

| Layer | Rule |
|-------|------|
| Login gate | `app_metadata.role === 'admin'` only (`isAdminUser` in `src/lib/supabase.ts`) |
| Session check | Prefer `auth.getUser()` over `getSession()` for gate checks (validates JWT server-side) |
| Consultant | `staff_role` enum + `staff_profiles.role` exist for future RBAC — **do not** widen login until RBAC is designed |
| API middleware | Validates Supabase JWT + admin role + **requires `staff_profiles` row** |
| Bootstrap | `AdminBootstrapService` creates auth user + profile; `ensureStaffProfileForAdmins()` runs every startup |

On login, `signInAsAdmin` calls `ensureStaffProfile` (client insert if row missing). Backend startup backfill is the fallback.

Missing profile on API routes → `401 Staff profile not found`. Fix: sign in again (client bootstrap) or restart backend.

## Leads and notes

- **Leads = `students` table** — no separate leads entity
- **Notes = `student_notes`** — one-to-many per student; full CRUD via `/api/admin/students/:id/notes`
- Dashboard list includes `latest_note`; full history in `LeadNotesModal`
- Note author: use `req.auth.email` (not raw `sub` unless aliased)

## Staff profiles

- Table: `staff_profiles` (1:1 with `auth.users.id`)
- **SPA canonical:** `getStaffProfile`, `updateStaffProfile`, `ensureStaffProfile` in `src/lib/admin/profile.ts` — direct Supabase with RLS
- **Backend fallback:** `GET/PATCH /api/admin/me` still exists for API consumers and middleware consistency
- **Insert RLS:** `staff_profiles_insert_own` — `auth.uid() = id` and `app_metadata.role = 'admin'`
- **Email change:** `supabase.auth.updateUser({ email })` on client (confirmation required), then sync to `staff_profiles` via `updateStaffProfile` when session email updates — do not update profile email before JWT reflects the new address
- Default bootstrap names: `ADMIN_FIRST_NAME` / `ADMIN_LAST_NAME` (Paul / Benn)
- Password reset: `requestPasswordReset` on login page — redirect URL must be in Supabase Auth allowlist (`/enrollify-manage/login`)

## Env separation

- Browser: `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` + `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` only
- Server: `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `ADMIN_*`, `AI_PROVIDER_ENCRYPTION_KEY` in `apps/backend/.env` — never `VITE_*`

## UI patterns

- Layout: `AdminShell` sidebar + `<Outlet />`
- Errors: `ErrorBanner` with optional retry
- Modals: lightweight fixed overlay (see `LeadNotesModal`) — no modal library unless justified
- Hidden from public nav; `robots.txt` disallows `/enrollify-manage`
